				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Act of Desperation<a name="52079"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 15 04 10:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ever been in a situation where the Ma is dead, the SA is dead, rampage tanks died instantly, the non-named tanks are all dead trying to hold aggro but the clerics dont know who to heal?
<br />

<br />
People start dying around you, mob is twirling in every direction destroying the melees with enrage and ripostes.
<br />

<br />
And then....you draw aggro.
<br />

<br />
But your prepared! You disc deftdance and laugh as the mob tries to nail you but you move too quickly. In the back of your mind you know you only have 12 seconds longer to live.
<br />

<br />
Last night I was on a AoW PU raid of about 35 people and we wiped at 15% on the Avatar of War. I Disced Deftdance at 16% and the raid was able to shell out a wopping 1% damage on the AoW before my 12 seconds were up(they were pretty much all dead already, I faded a couple times during the fight so I was low on the list).
<br />

<br />
Anywho, I'm curious what mobs/raids people have &quot;12seconded&quot; as a last ditch effort to prolong a lost fight. 
<br />

<br />
EDIT: hmm your right, checked around and most sources say 11-12seconds. Wonder why I always thought it was 18.</span></td>
