			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Act of Desperation<a name="52114"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 15 04 12:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We were up clearing all the nameds in Plane of Fire one day and we were taking on Arch Mage Yozanni. One of the tougher mobs in Fire but still not as hard as Reparm or Fennin, we expected a routine fight with the MA backed into a corner.
<br />

<br />
Either he didn't get slowed fast enough, or a cleric missed a CH or something, but unexpectedly our MA goes down. Tanks start desperately trying to get aggro, and raid chat flies by as clerics frantically try to figure out who to heal next. Tanks drop at the rate of one every few seconds. Very soon we have 10 dead tanks at Yozanni's feet and some very upset clerics with wrecked nerves.
<br />

<br />
We are now all facing Yozanni since no one has been able to establish solid aggro and get behind him yet. I just keep fighting.
<br />

<br />
He ripostes on me once, and brings my health down to 52% from full. I quickly realizes that if he ripostes on me again, he'll probably nearly kill me and I'll get low HP aggro. I get ready for deftdance, with my finger ready to click the button for it.
<br />

<br />
A few seconds later, the riposte I was expecting came. Suddenly I was at 6% health. Ultrafast, I hit deftdance just in time to see Yozanni <i>flipping out</i> on me, flailing wildly with both arms. My chat window that I use for combat scrolls by too fast to read, but every line ends with &quot;but YOU dodge!&quot; Hehehe. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Clerics were far too busy to heal a bard rather than a tank or a dps, which worked out rather nicely. It bought us the 12 seconds we needed for our last good tank to get in behind Yozanni and acheive aggro. We might have had 10 dead tanks at our feet, but we had managed to get someone there who could take the hits until the big guy died.
<br />

<br />
That was the first time I ever saved a raid with deftdance. It felt good to be useful for something other than resists and mana.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
